in linux we call folders 'directories' so learning how to move through these directories :
pwd-stands for 'printing working directory' it tells you which directory youre currently in 
cd stands for 'change directory' 
ls stands for list, it shows all the files and directories in your current location 
in linux / is the root of the file system [like c: in windows]
directories are seperated by / and not \ like in windows 
